                                                                                      "content": "Now I can see the exact issue! Looking at lines 424-429 in the `_tokenize_source` function:\n\n```python\nif content.strip().startswith('#'):\n    token_name, hex_val = _create_token(content, token_counter, current_hash)\n    token_map[hex_val] = content\n    processed_lines.append(indentation + 'pass' + hex_val)  # <-- THE PROBLEM\n    token_counter += 1\n    continue\n```\n\nThe problem is on line 427. When a line contains only a comment (like `        # Insert here`), the tokenization logic:\n\n1. Detects it's a comment-only line \n2. Creates a token for the comment content (`# Insert here`)\n3. **Replaces the entire line with `pass` + token** instead of preserving the original structure\n\nSo `        # Insert here` becomes `        pass__TOKEN__99ed3e78_0__`, which when detokenized becomes `        pass# Insert here`.\n\nThe line matching logic in `_handle_insertion` is looking for the exact string `# Insert here`, but it finds `pass# Insert here` instead.\n\nLet me fix this by modifying the tokenization to preserve standalone comments properly:",
                                                                                      "pending_results": [],
                                                                                      "role": "assistant",
                                                                                      "tool_calls": [
