                                                                                                                                              "content": "I see the issue! The comment `# marker` is being converted to a string literal `'# marker'` instead of staying as a comment. This is happening because the AST unparsing is treating the tokenized string literal differently.\n\nLooking at the debug output:\n- Expected: `# marker`\n- Actual: `'# marker'`\n\nThe problem is that when AST unparses a string literal like `\"\"\"__TOKEN__99ed3e78_0__\"\"\"`, it's converting it to a single-quoted string `'# marker'` instead of preserving it as a triple-quoted string that we can detect and replace.\n\nLet me check what's happening in the AST unparsing:",
