                                                                                                                                                     {
                                                                                                                                                      "content": "Perfect! Now I can see exactly what's happening:\n\n1. **Tokenized**: `\"\"\"__TOKEN__f721a1cf_0__\"\"\"` (triple-quoted string)\n2. **AST Constant**: `'__TOKEN__f721a1cf_0__'` (the AST stores just the token value)\n3. **AST Unparsed**: `'__TOKEN__f721a1cf_0__'` (single-quoted string)\n4. **Detokenized**: `'# marker'` (becomes a string literal instead of a comment)\n\nThe issue is that AST unparsing converts our triple-quoted string to a single-quoted string, so our detokenization logic that looks for `\"\"\"__TOKEN__\"\"\"` pattern doesn't match.\n\nI need to update the detokenization logic to handle both triple-quoted and single-quoted patterns:",
                                                                                                                                                      "pending_results": [],
                                                                                                                                                      "role": "assistant",
                                                                                                                                                      "tool_calls": [
                                                                                                                                                       {
                                                                                                                                                        "type": "tool_use",
                                                                                                                                                        "id": "toolu_01DxNaLSRp2dWXkjYakHyz63",
                                                                                                                                                        "name": "replace_function",
                                                                                                                                                        "input": {
                                                                                                                                                         "file_path": "bots/tools/python_edit.py",
                                                                                                                                                         "new_function_def": "\n                                                                                                            def _detokenize_source(tokenized_source: str, token_map: Dict[str, str]) -> str:\n                                                                                                                \"\"\"\n                                                                                                                Restore original source from tokenized version.\n                                                                                                            \n                                                                                                                Handles proper indentation of multiline content.\n                                                                                                                \"\"\"\n                                                                                                                result = tokenized_source\n                                                                                                                for token_value, original in token_map.items():\n                                                                                                                    while token_value in result:\n                                                                                                                        start = result.find(token_value)\n                                                                                                                        if start == -1:\n                                                                                                                            break\n                                                                                                                        \n                                                                                                                        # Check if this token is part of a standalone comment pattern\n                                                                                                                        # Could be \"\"\"__TOKEN__\"\"\" or '__TOKEN__' or \"__TOKEN__\"\n                                                                                                                        line_start = result.rfind('\\n', 0, start) + 1\n                                                                                                                        line_end = result.find('\\n', start)\n                                                                                                                        if line_end == -1:\n                                                                                                                            line_end = len(result)\n                                                                                                                        line = result[line_start:line_end]\n                                                                                                                        \n                                                                                                                        # Check if this line matches any standalone comment pattern\n                                                                                                                        line_stripped = line.strip()\n                                                                                                                        is_standalone_comment = (\n                                                                                                                            line_stripped == f'\"\"\"{token_value}\"\"\"' or\n                                                                                                                            line_stripped == f\"'{token_value}'\" or\n                                                                                                                            line_stripped == f'\"{token_value}\"'\n                                                                                                                        )\n                                                                                                                        \n                                                                                                                        if is_standalone_comment:\n                                                                                                                            # This is a standalone comment - replace the entire string literal\n                                                                                                                            indent = line[:len(line) - len(line.lstrip())]\n                                                                                                                            replacement = indent + original\n                                                                                                                            result = result[:line_start] + replacement + result[line_end:]\n                                                                                                                        else:\n                                                                                                                            # Regular token replacement\n                                                                                                                            if '\\n' in original:\n                                                                                                                                indent = _get_indentation_at_position(result, start)\n                                                                                                                                indented = _indent_multiline_content(original, indent)\n                                                                                                                                result = result[:start] + indented + result[start + len(token_value):]\n                                                                                                                            else:\n                                                                                                                                result = result[:start] + original + result[start + len(token_value):]\n                                                                                                                return result"
                                                                                                                                                        }
                                                                                                                                                       }
                                                                                                                                                      ],
