                                                                                                                                                                                             {
                                                                                                                                                                                              "content": "Sure! The issue was in the inline comment tokenization logic. Let me explain what was happening and how I fixed it:\n\n## The Problem\n\nWhen we had code like:\n```python\nx = 1  # comment one\n```\n\nThe original tokenization logic was:\n1. Find the `#` at position (let's say position 5)\n2. Split into:\n   - `code = processed_line[:comment_start].rstrip()` \u2192 `\"x = 1\"` (removed trailing spaces)\n   - `comment = processed_line[comment_start:]` \u2192 `\"# comment one\"`\n3. Create token and combine: `code + hex_val` \u2192 `\"x = 1__TOKEN__f0935d98_0__\"`\n\nThis created an **invalid Python identifier** `1__TOKEN__...` because there was no space between the number `1` and the token that starts with letters.\n\n## The Fix\n\nI changed this line:\n```python\n# Before (WRONG):\ncode = processed_line[:comment_start].rstrip()  # Removes trailing spaces\n\n# After (CORRECT):\ncode = processed_line[:comment_start]  # Keeps trailing spaces\n```\n\nNow the same example becomes:\n1. `code = \"x = 1  \"` (keeps the two spaces)\n2. `comment = \"# comment one\"`\n3. Result: `\"x = 1  __TOKEN__f0935d98_0__\"` (valid Python with proper spacing)\n\n## Why This Matters\n\nThe AST parser needs valid Python syntax. `x = 1__TOKEN__` looks like a malformed number literal to Python, but `x = 1  __TOKEN__` is clearly separate tokens (a number, whitespace, and an identifier).\n\nLet's test the fix:",
                                                                                                                                                                                              "pending_results": [],
                                                                                                                                                                                              "role": "assistant",
